SIMPLE: gent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gent
<hw>Gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>gent</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>genitus</ets> born, or (less prob.) fr. <ets>gentilis</ets>. See
<er>Genteel</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Gentle; noble; of gentle birth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All of a knight [who] was fair and <qex>gent</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Neat; pretty; fine; elegant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her body <qex>gent</qex> and small.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Genteel</ent>⟦br⟧
